    {
      "title": "Introduction",
      "description": "Hi there! This is a guided tour to help you about Verifiable Credentials. We will build a Workshop Attendee Credential in JavaScript. We will create a self-signed VC where you're attesting that you attended the workshop.\n\nPress `Next` to to get started ðŸ‘‡"
    },
    {
      "file": "package.json",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "Run `npm install` to install the web5/credentials package and the web5/dids package, so we can start building. \n\nPress `Next` to to get continue ðŸ‘‡"
    },
    {
      "file": "index.js",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "For each actor participating in the Verifiable Credential -- the issuer, the holder (sometimes called subject), and the verifier. We need some kind of identifier for each participating person. In the Web5 ecosystem, we use Decentralized Identifiers -- a W3C standard. These are globally unique identifiers.\n\nPress `Next` to to get continue ðŸ‘‡"
    },
    {
      "file": "index.js",
      "line": 14,
      "description": "We already handle creating the Decentralized Identifier for you, so you don't have to create it yourself, but you can take a look at how we do it. We use `DidDht.create()` to create a Decentralized Identifier.\n\nPress `Next` to to get continue ðŸ‘‡"
    },
    {
      "file": "index.js",
      "line": 24,
      "description": "Run `node index.js` in your terminal, so we can see the contents of our Decentralized Identifier.\n\nPress `Next` to to get continue ðŸ‘‡"
    },
    {
      "file": "index.js",
      "line": 28,
      "description": "Now, let's create a variable to hold our Verifiable Credential using `const vc =`. \n\nPress `Next` to to get continue ðŸ‘‡"
    },
    {
      "file": "index.js",
      "line": 28,
      "description": "Let's use the Verifiable Credential package. Assign the `vc` variable that you made to `await VerifiableCredential.create({}) \n\nPress `Next` to to get continue ðŸ‘‡"
    },
    {
      "file": "index.js",
      "line": 29,
      "description": "Set the type of credential to `'type': 'WorkshopAttendeeCredential'`. This field is important. The verifier is looking for this exact value. \n\nPress `Next` to to get continue ðŸ‘‡"
    },
    {
      "file": "index.js",
      "line": 30,
      "description": "Set the issuer to `'issuer': 'attendeeDid.uri'`. \n\nPress `Next` to to get continue ðŸ‘‡"
    },
    {
      "file": "index.js",
      "line": 31,
      "description": "Set the subject to `'subject': 'attendeeDid.uri'`. \n\nPress `Next` to to get continue ðŸ‘‡"
    },
    {
      "file": "index.js",
      "line": 31,
      "description": "Expiration Date is an optional field. We can give this an expiration date of when you can no longer use this VC to retrieve swag. Set the expirationDate to `'expirationDate': '2024-12-31T23:59:59Z',`. \n\nPress `Next` to to get continue ðŸ‘‡"
    },
    {
      "file": "index.js",
      "line": 32,
      "description": "Create a data object where we will store additional information and claims about the subject receiving the credential `data: {}`. \n\nPress `Next` to to get continue ðŸ‘‡"
    },
    {
      "file": "index.js",
      "line": 33,
      "description": "In our data object, we want to set the name of the subject, location, conference, eventDate, and issuerName. \n\nPress `Next` to to get continue ðŸ‘‡"
    },
    {
      "file": "index.js",
      "line": 34,
      "description": "Log our vc to see how it looks! \n\nPress `Next` to to get continue ðŸ‘‡"
